Nicholas Jubber was born in England in 1977. After graduating Oxford, he had been teaching in Jerusalem for two weeks when the Second Intifada broke out.
Nicholas Jubber's journeys have taken him to the Ethiopian highlands, the Afghan lowlands, the heart of the Sahara, and many other places.
